  "summaries": [
    {
      "actionDate": "2025-02-13",
      "actionDesc": "Introduced in Senate",
      "text": "<p><strong>Helping Eliminate Limitations for Prompt Response and Recovery Act or the HELP Response and Recovery Act</strong></p><p>This bill extends the maximum duration of noncompetitive Department of Homeland Security (DHS) contracts for disaster response and recovery from 150 days to one year by repealing a current limitation on such DHS contracts so that standard procurement regulations apply regarding urgent needs. It also requires&nbsp;DHS to report to Congress annually for five years to review how this repeal has prevented waste and provide information on noncompetitive Federal Emergency Management Agency contracts.</p>",
      "updateDate": "2025-06-24T13:00:05Z",
      "versionCode": "00"
    }
  ]
